The paper proposes a methodology to detect drones using network traffic analysis. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with identifying potential threats. The methodology involves analyzing communication traffic, which is a key aspect of computer networks (cs.NI). The authors also apply classification algorithms, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the solution, which involves evaluating the results using statistical analysis, a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for future research in the area, which involves developing new techniques and algorithms for drone detection, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
